      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "CHOIR POINT (1) resumes for her second campaign having shown good ability in three runs last time in, a winner on debut before tackling two very strong races and finishing on the heels of the placegetters. She's very well suited this level fresh and might just be too classy. SHE DARESTHE DEVIL (4) was dominant when last seen at Sale in easier company, charging home to score by four lengths. Have to respect off that. MAYA'S ACE (5) found the line well fresh and can improve. We'll get a guide to that form earlier through Logam who looks well placed in Race 2. Expect she can go on with it. ENDLESS FOREVERS (2) ran well fresh at Ballarat and should be in this for a long way with that run under the belt.",
